<br>
If you get the right god all the things that can see invis love you anyway so its all good :-)<br>
<br>
I have to disagree that it is easy to drag a bod out from the bottom. I have done cr in the hole a few times and I never did work out how to do it from bottom with 1 rogue.<br>
<br>
Used to do it with my partner so we could over come drop offs. Still I suppose you can get around drop off by dieing repeatedly.<br>
<br>
The bottom of the hole is a fun amazing journey, so many different types of environments in there :-) The lucky rogue will also get to find and see all the nice safe spots to fight in :-)<br>
<br>
All in all if you are neutral for your goodness I would go to talk to FaF as they are probably going to be a lot more resonsive than a guide and get them to ether mount a rescue mission of coffin your butt out :-)<br>
<br>
I dread that drop off every time I auto follow past it :-)<br>
<br>
As to the guides not helping, well if they helped every time we got ourselves stuck Norath would feel like a game with little consequences, as long as there are options they should not get involved. And yes I have almost cried in fear when &quot;fear&quot; went wrong and it took 5 hours to get our bodies back :-) thought I had lost it that time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
All in all ya know, I am really glad we have 1 nice big ubber guild on the server :-) especially as they seem very nice :-) When us smaller folk get wiped real hard multiple times somewhere it is nice to have an option before all the bodies rot :-)<br>
